The paper discusses the development of an Integrated Crowd Management Support System based on Collective Artificial Intelligence approach. The system involves the use of software tools for the analysis of pedestrian and crowd behavior, which suggests the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
